"use strict";(self.webpackChunk_N_E=self.webpackChunk_N_E||[]).push([[788],{2788:function(e,t,a){a.r(t),a.d(t,{SEASICK:function(){return o}});let o={id:"seasick",title:"The Seasick Pirate",shortDescription:"A wrongly accused baker who hates the ocean.",skillGrid:{exploration:["star","open","open","star","blocked","blocked","blocked"],brawn:["star","open","open","star","star","blocked","blocked"],hunting:["star","star","open","blocked","blocked","blocked","blocked"],aim:["star","star","blocked","blocked","blocked","blocked","blocked"],swagger:["open","open","star","star","blocked","blocked","blocked"],navigation:["star","open","open","star","star","star","blocked"]},constellation:a(9774).cr,storyBlanks:[{number:1,prompt:"A baked good",type:"text"},{number:2,prompt:"The pirate name of another player",type:"player_name"},{number:3,prompt:"A gross bodily function",type:"text"},{number:4,prompt:"Something that calms you down",type:"text"},{number:5,prompt:"A crime you did not commit",type:"text"}],backstory:"I am a baker! A BAKER! I should be elbow-deep in dough right now, crafting the perfect {1}, not hanging over the side of a pirate ship trying not to {3}! But here I am, thanks to a terrible misunderstanding.\n\nYou see, I was falsely accused of {5}. I didn't do it! I was in my bakery the entire time, making {1}(s)! But did anyone believe me? No! The constable said my hands were \"suspiciously clean\" for someone who claimed to have been baking all day, which I'll have you know is a COMPLIMENT to my hygiene, not evidence of criminality!\n\nI fled to the docks and stowed away on the first ship I could find, which turned out to be a pirate vessel. By the time I was discovered, we were already at sea. The captain offered me a choice: join the crew or swim home. I can't swim. I can barely float. The ocean is my mortal enemy. Every wave is a personal attack on my digestive system.\n\n{2} seems amused by my constant misery. They like to describe meals in graphic detail just to watch me turn green. I spend most of my time clutching my stomach and thinking about {4}, which is the only thing that keeps me from completely losing it.",events:[{narrative:"Despite my constant nausea, I managed to bake {1}(s) using the ship's terrible supplies. The crew went absolutely wild. Apparently they've been eating hardtack for months. Even the captain came to thank me personally. {2} asked for seconds. I gave them the burnt one.",effect:"Supplies +3. Discontent -1."},{narrative:"I found a remedy for seasickness at the last port! It smells like {4} and tastes like feet, but it actually works! For the first time in months, I can stand upright without wanting to {3}. I feel like a new person!",effect:"Retrieve card 57 Anti-Nausea Tonic from the story deck."},{narrative:"A storm hit last night and I thought I was going to die. I was thrown around the cabin like a ragdoll, {3}ing at every impact. When it finally passed, I found myself lying on the deck, staring at the stars. For one brief, beautiful moment, the sea was calm and I didn't feel sick at all. It was almost... peaceful. Then the ship rocked and I {3}ed again.",effect:"Re-roll +2. Gain 1 skill of your choice."},{narrative:"{2} and I had an actual conversation today that didn't involve them making fun of me. They told me about their life before pirating, and I told them about my bakery. They said my {1}(s) are the best thing they've ever eaten. I think that might be the nicest thing anyone on this cursed ship has ever said to me.",effect:"Crew +1. Discontent -1."},{narrative:"I received word that the real criminal who committed the {5} has been caught! I'm a free person! I could leave this ship and go home! But... I don't know. The crew has grown on me. And they really do need someone who can bake a decent {1}. Maybe I'll stay a bit longer. Just a bit. If my stomach can handle it.",effect:"Re-roll +3. Infamy +1."}],endings:{bad:{threshold:"≤3",text:"The sea wins. After months of constant {3}ing, you finally can't take it anymore and beg the captain to drop you off at the nearest port. They dump you on a tiny island with nothing but a sack of flour and a bad attitude. You build a small bakery out of driftwood and sell {1}(s) to the occasional passing ship. It's not the worst life, but every time you look at the ocean, you feel your stomach churn. {2} stops by once and tries to cheer you up by doing an impression of you {3}ing during the great storm. You do not find it funny. You throw a {1} at their head. You spend the rest of your days baking on solid ground, which is all you ever really wanted."},good:{threshold:"4",text:'With your name finally cleared, you return home to reopen your bakery. But to your surprise, you find you actually miss certain aspects of pirate life — the camaraderie, the adventure, and yes, even {2}\'s terrible jokes. You expand your bakery into a chain called "{1}s & Scallywags," themed after your pirating days. The signature dish is a {1} shaped like a pirate ship. {2} visits regularly and eats their weight in baked goods every time. Your seasickness never fully goes away, but you keep a bottle of the tonic behind the counter, and on calm days, you sometimes sail out to the harbor. Just for a few minutes. Just to remind yourself that you survived.'},legendary:{threshold:"5",text:"Against all odds, you become the most famous pirate baker in history. Your {1}(s) become legendary, sought after by pirates and royals alike. You open a floating bakery — a ship modified so that the kitchen is stabilized and the motion is minimal. You call it The {1} of the Seven Seas. Pirates come from across the world to buy your baked goods, and your ship becomes a neutral zone where even rival crews eat side by side in peace. {2} becomes your first mate and official taste tester. Your {3} problem? Completely cured, thanks to a lifetime of exposure and a never-ending supply of the tonic. You even learn to swim. Sort of. You can doggy paddle. The sea is no longer your enemy — it's your kitchen. And there's no better feeling in the world than baking a perfect {1} while watching the sunrise over an endless ocean."}}}}}]);